http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/%E2%80%98Sharing-FB-post-an-error%E2%80%99/article14018343.ece

Associate Professor in the University of Hyderabad Raghava Reddy in a clarification issued here on Sunday has said that sharing of the Facebook post on the suicide of research scholar Rohith was an inadvertent error.Responding to a news report published in these columns on Sunday, Prof Raghava Reddy said he was pained at the reference to him. Clarifying the issue he said: “ I never intended to share it. While scrolling down the Facebook on my touch screen Phone the share button was hit.”“After seeing it being commented I realised the error and removed from my Facebook wall. ,” he said